Source:  Resolution Journal of J.R. Forster, The
Author:  FORSTER
Vol / Page:  2/203
Edition:
Quote:  It had a yellowish beak & <i>Capt Cook</i> says Mr <i>Banks</i> has seen it near <i>Cape Horn</i> in the high southen latitudes, & called it <i>Mother Cary's Goose</i>. [[ed. fn] Giant Petrel <i>Macronectes giganteus </i>(Gmelin, 1789).] It must be observed that the Sailors call all the <i>Procellarias, Mother Cary's Chickens fowls,</i> ducks, pigeons, Geese etc. [sic] in proportion to their Size.
