Author:  WILLIAMS
Vol / Page:  119
Edition:  1961
Quote:  As it came on to rain we were obliged to haul to the wind, and stood off till towards morning. Mother Kary's Chickens playing about all day.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1873
Source:  Birds of New Zealand
Author:  BULLER
Vol / Page:  230
Edition:
Quote:  I found ... that seamen make no distinction between this species of Storm-Petrel

[<i>Thalassidroma melanogaster</i>, Black-bellied Storm-petrel], and its congeners, calling them all `Mother Carey's Chickens', and resenting as a positive sin any attempt to shoot or capture these `spirits of departed sailors', as they facetiously term them, to whom they profess to commit the destinies of the voyage.
